        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 8 at 1:02AM CDT until June 8 at 2:00AM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>SVRSHV

The National Weather Service in Shreveport has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southeastern Lafayette County in southwestern Arkansas...
Southwestern Columbia County in southwestern Arkansas...
Northwestern Webster Parish in northwestern Louisiana...
Northeastern Bossier Parish in northwestern Louisiana...

* Until 200 AM CDT.

* At 101 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Canfield, or
9 miles south of Lewisville, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Springhill, Cullen, Sarepta, Bradley, Taylor, Bussey, Canfield,
Welcome, Lerch, McKamie, Walkerville, Cornelius, State Line,
Horsehead, and Mars Hill.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
